measure.CatchLine: Limits the applicant screening charge a residential landlord may collect to $20.
measure.MeasureSummary:
Digest: This Act caps screening fees paid by residential tenants. (Flesch Readability Score: 66.1). 
	Limits the applicant screening charge a residential landlord may collect to $20. Extends certain screening requirements to include landlords who do not collect an applicant screening charge. Allows landlords to alternatively accept third-party screening reports provided by an applicant.
measure.RelatingToFull: Relating to residential applicant screening charges; amending ORS 90.295.
measure.RelatingTo: Relating to residential applicant screening charges.
measure.FiscalImpact: May have fiscal impact, but no statement yet issued
measure.RevenueImpact: May have revenue impact, but no statement yet issued

historyActions.ActionText: First reading. Referred to Speaker's desk.
